messages.name: Application
messages.description: Application is the message that defines an Application in the network.

fields.name: collaborator
fields.description: Collaborator to grant all rights on the newly created application.

messages.name: ListApplicationsRequest
messages.description:
By default we list all applications the caller has rights on.
Set the user or the organization (not both) to instead list the applications
where the user or organization is collaborator on.

methods.name: UpdateAPIKey
methods.description:
Update the rights of an existing application API key. To generate an API key,
the CreateAPIKey should be used. To delete an API key, update it
with zero rights.

methods.name: SetCollaborator
methods.description: Setting a collaborator without rights, removes them.

methods.name: Create
methods.description:
Create a new application. This also sets the given organization or user as
first collaborator with all possible rights.

methods.name: Get
methods.description:
Get the application with the given identifiers, selecting the fields given
by the field mask. The method may return more or less fields, depending on
the rights of the caller.

methods.name: List
methods.description: List applications. See request message for details.

services.name: AppAs
services.description: The AppAs service connects an application or integration to an Application Server.

services.name: As
services.description: The As service manages the Application Server.

services.name: AsDeviceRegistry
services.description: The AsDeviceRegistry service allows clients to manage their end devices on the Application Server.

methods.name: Get
methods.description:
Get returns the device that matches the given identifiers.
If there are multiple matches, an error will be returned.

methods.name: Set
methods.description: Set creates or updates the device.

methods.name: Delete
methods.description:
Delete deletes the device that matches the given identifiers.
If there are multiple matches, an error will be returned.

enums.name: GrantType
enums.description: The OAuth2 flows an OAuth client can use to get an access token.

values.name: GRANT_AUTHORIZATION_CODE
values.description: Grant type used to exchange an authorization code for an access token.

values.name: GRANT_PASSWORD
values.description: Grant type used to exchange a user ID and password for an access token.

values.name: GRANT_REFRESH_TOKEN
values.description: Grant type used to exchange a refresh token for an access token.

messages.name: Client
messages.description: An OAuth client on the network.

fields.name: secret
fields.description: The client secret is only visible to collaborators of the client.

fields.name: redirect_uris
fields.description:
The allowed redirect URIs against which authorization requests are checked.
If the authorization request does not pass a redirect URI, the first one
from this list is taken.
fields.label: repeated

fields.name: state
fields.description:
The reviewing state of the client.
This field can only be modified by admins.

fields.name: skip_authorization
fields.description:
If set, the authorization page will be skipped.
This field can only be modified by admins.

fields.name: endorsed
fields.description:
If set, the authorization page will show endorsement.
This field can only be modified by admins.

fields.name: grants
fields.description:
OAuth flows that can be used for the client to get a token.
After a client is created, this field can only be modified by admins.
fields.label: repeated

fields.name: rights
fields.description:
Rights denotes what rights the client will have access to.
Users that previously authorized this client will have to re-authorize the
client after rights are added to this list.
fields.label: repeated

fields.name: collaborator
fields.description: Collaborator to grant all rights on the newly created client.

messages.name: ListClientsRequest
messages.description:
By default we list all OAuth clients the caller has rights on.
Set the user or the organization (not both) to instead list the OAuth clients
where the user or organization is collaborator on.

methods.name: SetCollaborator
methods.description:
Set the rights of a collaborator on the OAuth client. Users or organizations
are considered to be a collaborator if they have at least one right on the
OAuth client.

methods.name: Create
methods.description:
Create a new OAuth client. This also sets the given organization or user as
first collaborator with all possible rights.

methods.name: Get
methods.description:
Get the OAuth client with the given identifiers, selecting the fields given
by the field mask. The method may return more or less fields, depending on
the rights of the caller.

methods.name: List
methods.description: List OAuth clients. See request message for details.

messages.name: PeerInfo
messages.description: PeerInfo

fields.name: grpc_port
fields.description: Port on which the gRPC server is exposed.

fields.name: tls
fields.description: Indicates whether the gRPC server uses TLS.

fields.name: roles
fields.description: Roles of the peer ()
fields.label: repeated

fields.name: tags
fields.description: Tags of the peer
fields.label: repeated

messages.name: EndDevice
messages.description:
Defines an End Device registration and its state on the network.
The persistence of the EndDevice is divided between the Network Server, Application Server and Join Server.
SDKs are responsible for combining (if desired) the three.

fields.name: name
fields.description: Friendly name of the device. Stored in Application Server.

fields.name: description
fields.description: Description of the device. Stored in Application Server.

fields.name: attributes
fields.description: Attributes of the device. Stored in Application Server.
fields.label: repeated

fields.name: version_ids
fields.description: Version Identifiers. Stored in Application Server.

fields.name: service_profile_id
fields.description: Default service profile. Stored in Network Server.

fields.name: supports_class_b
fields.description:
Whether the device supports class B.
Copied on creation from template identified by version_ids, if any or from the home Network Server device profile, if any.

fields.name: supports_class_c
fields.description:
Whether the device supports class C.
Copied on creation from template identified by version_ids, if any or from the home Network Server device profile, if any.

fields.name: lorawan_version
fields.description:
LoRaWAN MAC version. Stored in Network Server.
Copied on creation from template identified by version_ids, if any or from the home Network Server device profile, if any.

fields.name: lorawan_phy_version
fields.description:
LoRaWAN PHY version. Stored in Network Server.
Copied on creation from template identified by version_ids, if any or from the home Network Server device profile, if any.

fields.name: frequency_plan_id
fields.description:
ID of the frequency plan used by this device.
Copied on creation from template identified by version_ids, if any or from the home Network Server device profile, if any.

fields.name: default_mac_parameters
fields.description:
Default MAC layer parameters, to which device is reset by default (e.g. on join or ResetInd). Stored in Network Server.
Copied on creation from template identified by version_ids, if any or from the home Network Server device profile, if any.

fields.name: min_frequency
fields.description:
Minimum frequency the device is capable of using (Hz). Stored in Network Server.
Copied on creation from template identified by version_ids, if any or from the home Network Server device profile, if any.

fields.name: max_frequency
fields.description:
Maximum frequency the device is capable of using (Hz). Stored in Network Server.
Copied on creation from template identified by version_ids, if any or from the home Network Server device profile, if any.

fields.name: resets_f_cnt
fields.description:
Whether the device resets the frame counters (not LoRaWAN compliant). Stored in Network Server.
Copied on creation from template identified by version_ids, if any or from the home Network Server device profile, if any.

fields.name: uses_32_bit_f_cnt
fields.description:
Whether the device uses 32-bit frame counters. Stored in Network Server.
Copied on creation from template identified by version_ids, if any or from the home Network Server device profile, if any.

fields.name: supports_join
fields.description:
The device supports join (it's OTAA).
Copied on creation from template identified by version_ids, if any or from the home Network Server device profile, if any.

fields.name: resets_join_nonces
fields.description:
Whether the device resets the join and dev nonces (not LoRaWAN 1.1 compliant). Stored in Network Server.
Copied on creation from template identified by version_ids, if any or from the home Network Server device profile, if any.

fields.name: root_keys
fields.description: Device root keys. Stored in Join Server.

fields.name: network_server_address
fields.description: The address (host:port) of the Network Server associated with this device. Stored in Join Server.

fields.name: application_server_address
fields.description: The address (host:port) of the Application Server associated with this device. Stored in Join Server.

fields.name: net_id
fields.description:
Home NetID. Stored in Join Server.

NOTE: Join Server address can be derived from join EUI.

fields.name: mac_settings
fields.description: Settings for how the Network Server handles MAC for this device. Stored in Network Server.

fields.name: mac_state
fields.description: MAC state of the device. Stored in Network Server.

fields.name: session
fields.description: Current session. Stored in Network Server.

fields.name: session_fallback
fields.description: Fallback session. Stored in Network Server until RekeyInd is received.

fields.name: next_dev_nonce
fields.description:
Next DevNonce to be expected (in case of LoRaWAN 1.1).
Stored in Join Server.

fields.name: used_dev_nonces
fields.description:
Used DevNonces (in case of LoRaWAN 1.0).
Stored in Join Server.
fields.label: repeated

fields.name: next_join_nonce
fields.description:
Next JoinNonce/AppNonce to be used (in case of LoRaWAN 1.1).
Stored in Join Server.

fields.name: used_join_nonces
fields.description:
Used JoinNonces/AppNonce (in case of LoRaWAN 1.0).
Stored in Join Server.
fields.label: repeated

fields.name: next_rj_count_0
fields.description:
Next Rejoin counter (type 0/2) to be expected.
Stored in Join Server.

fields.name: next_rj_count_1
fields.description:
Next Rejoin counter (type 1) to be expected.
Stored in Join Server.

fields.name: next_status_after
fields.description:
Number of messages, after which a new DevStatus MAC command shall be scheduled.
Stored in Network Server.

fields.name: last_status_received_at
fields.description:
Time when the device status was last received via the DevStatus MAC command.
Stored in Network Server.

fields.name: power_state
fields.description:
The power state of the device; whether it is battery-powered or connected to an external power source.
Received via the DevStatus MAC command at status_received_at.
Stored in Network Server.

fields.name: battery_percentage
fields.description:
Latest-known battery percentage of the device.
Received via the DevStatus MAC command at status_received_at or earlier.
Stored in Network Server.

fields.name: downlink_margin
fields.description:
Demodulation signal-to-noise ratio (dB).
Received via the DevStatus MAC command at status_received_at.
Stored in Network Server.

fields.name: recent_uplinks
fields.description:
Recent uplink messages sorted by time. Stored in Network Server.
The number of messages stored may depend on configuration.
fields.label: repeated

fields.name: recent_downlinks
fields.description:
Recent downlink messages sorted by time. Stored in Network Server.
The number of messages stored may depend on configuration.
fields.label: repeated

fields.name: queued_application_downlinks
fields.description:
Queued Application downlink messages. Stored in Application Server,
which sets them on the Network Server.
fields.label: repeated

fields.name: formatters
fields.description:
The payload formatters for this end device. Stored in Application Server.
Copied on creation from template identified by version_ids.

fields.name: locations
fields.description: Location of the device. Stored in Application Server.
fields.label: repeated

fields.name: logos
fields.description: Logos contains file names of brand logos.
fields.label: repeated

messages.description: Template for creating end devices.

fields.name: ids
fields.description: Version identifiers.

fields.name: lorawan_version
fields.description: LoRaWAN MAC version.

fields.name: lorawan_phy_version
fields.description: LoRaWAN PHY version.

fields.name: frequency_plan_id
fields.description: ID of the frequency plan used by this device.

fields.name: photos
fields.description: Photos contains file names of device photos.
fields.label: repeated

fields.name: supports_class_b
fields.description: Whether the device supports class B.

fields.name: supports_class_c
fields.description: Whether the device supports class C.

fields.name: default_mac_parameters
fields.description: Default MAC layer parameters, to which device is reset by default (e.g. on join or ResetInd).

fields.name: min_frequency
fields.description: Minimum frequency the device is capable of using (Hz).

fields.name: max_frequency
fields.description: Maximum frequency the device is capable of using (Hz).

fields.name: resets_f_cnt
fields.description: Whether the device resets the frame counters (not LoRaWAN compliant).

fields.name: uses_32_bit_f_cnt
fields.description: Whether the device uses 32-bit frame counters.

fields.name: supports_join
fields.description: The device supports join (it's OTAA).

fields.name: resets_join_nonces
fields.description: Whether the device resets the join and dev nonces (not LoRaWAN 1.1 compliant).

fields.name: default_formatters
fields.description: Default formatters defining the payload formats for this end device.

messages.name: EndDeviceVersionIdentifiers
messages.description: Identifies an end device model with version information.

messages.name: MACParameters
messages.description:
MACParameters represent the parameters of the device's MAC layer (active or desired).
This is used internally by the Network Server and is read only.

fields.name: max_eirp
fields.description: Maximum EIRP (dBm).

fields.name: uplink_dwell_time
fields.description: Uplink dwell time is set (400ms).

fields.name: downlink_dwell_time
fields.description: Downlink dwell time is set (400ms).

fields.name: adr_data_rate_index
fields.description: ADR: data rate index to use.

fields.name: adr_tx_power_index
fields.description: ADR: transmission power index to use.

fields.name: adr_nb_trans
fields.description: ADR: number of retransmissions.

fields.name: adr_ack_limit
fields.description: ADR: number of messages to wait before setting ADRAckReq.

fields.name: adr_ack_delay
fields.description: ADR: number of messages to wait after setting ADRAckReq and before changing TxPower or DataRate.

fields.name: rx1_delay
fields.description: Rx1 delay (Rx2 delay is Rx1 delay + 1 second).

fields.name: rx1_data_rate_offset
fields.description: Data rate offset for Rx1.

fields.name: rx2_data_rate_index
fields.description: Data rate index for Rx2.

fields.name: rx2_frequency
fields.description: Frequency for Rx2 (Hz).

fields.name: rejoin_time_periodicity
fields.description: Time within which a rejoin-request must be sent.

fields.name: rejoin_count_periodicity
fields.description: Message count within which a rejoin-request must be sent.

fields.name: max_duty_cycle
fields.description: Maximum uplink duty cycle (of all channels).

fields.name: channels
fields.description: Configured uplink channels and optionally Rx1 frequency.
fields.label: repeated

fields.name: ping_slot_frequency
fields.description: Frequency of the class B ping slot (Hz).

fields.name: ping_slot_data_rate_index
fields.description: Data rate index of the class B ping slot.

fields.name: beacon_frequency
fields.description: Frequency of the class B beacon (Hz).

fields.name: uplink_frequency
fields.description: Uplink frequency of the channel (Hz).

fields.name: downlink_frequency
fields.description: Downlink frequency of the channel (Hz).

fields.name: min_data_rate_index
fields.description: Index of the minimum data rate for uplink.

fields.name: max_data_rate_index
fields.description: Index of the maximum data rate for uplink.

fields.name: enable_uplink
fields.description: Channel can be used by device for uplink.

fields.name: adr_margin
fields.description:
The ADR margin tells the network server how much margin it should add in ADR requests.
A bigger margin is less efficient, but gives a better chance of successful reception.

fields.name: class_b_timeout
fields.description: Deadline for the device to respond to requests from the Network Server.

fields.name: class_c_timeout
fields.description: Deadline for the device to respond to requests from the Network Server.

fields.name: status_time_periodicity
fields.description: The interval after which a DevStatusReq MACCommand shall be sent.

fields.name: status_count_periodicity
fields.description: Number of uplink messages after which a DevStatusReq MACCommand shall be sent.

messages.name: MACState
messages.description:
MACState represents the state of MAC layer of the device.
MACState is reset on each join for OTAA or ResetInd for ABP devices.
This is used internally by the Network Server and is read only.

fields.name: current_parameters
fields.description: Current LoRaWAN MAC parameters.

fields.name: desired_parameters
fields.description: Desired LoRaWAN MAC parameters.

fields.name: device_class
fields.description:
Currently active LoRaWAN device class
- Device class is A by default
- If device sets ClassB bit in uplink, this will be set to B
- If device sent DeviceModeInd MAC message, this will be set to that value

fields.name: lorawan_version
fields.description: LoRaWAN MAC version.

fields.name: next_confirmed_downlink_at
fields.description: Time when a new confirmed downlink message or MAC command is ready to be scheduled for class C.

fields.name: ping_slot_periodicity
fields.description: Periodicity of the class B ping slot.

fields.name: pending_application_downlink
fields.description: A confirmed application downlink, for which an acknowledgment is expected to arrive.

fields.name: queued_responses
fields.description:
Queued MAC responses.
Regenerated on each uplink.
fields.label: repeated

fields.name: pending_requests
fields.description:
Pending MAC requests(i.e. sent requests, for which no response has been received yet).
Regenerated on each downlink.
fields.label: repeated

fields.name: dev_addr
fields.description:
Device Address, issued by the Network Server or chosen by device manufacturer in case of testing range (beginning with 00-03).
Known by Network Server, Application Server and Join Server. Owned by Network Server.

fields.name: next_f_cnt_up
fields.description: Next FCntUp to be expected. Network Server only. Application Server assumes the Network Server checked it.

fields.name: next_n_f_cnt_down
fields.description: Next NFCntDown to be used. Network Server only.

fields.name: next_a_f_cnt_down
fields.description: Next AFCntDown to be used. Application Server only.

fields.name: last_conf_f_cnt_down
fields.description: FCnt of the last confirmed downlink message sent. Network Server only.

fields.name: started_at
fields.description: Time when the session started. Network Server only.

values.name: DOWNLINK_PATH_CONSTRAINT_NONE
values.description: Indicates that the gateway can be selected for downlink without constraints by the Network Server.

values.name: DOWNLINK_PATH_CONSTRAINT_PREFER_OTHER
values.description: Indicates that the gateway can be selected for downlink only if no other or better gateway can be selected.

values.name: DOWNLINK_PATH_CONSTRAINT_NEVER
values.description: Indicates that this gateway will never be selected for downlink, even if that results in no available downlink path.

enums.name: State
enums.description: State enum defines states that an entity can be in.

values.name: STATE_REQUESTED
values.description: Denotes that the entity has been requested and is pending review by an admin.

values.name: STATE_APPROVED
values.description: Denotes that the entity has been reviewed and approved by an admin.

values.name: STATE_REJECTED
values.description: Denotes that the entity has been reviewed and rejected by an admin.

values.name: STATE_FLAGGED
values.description: Denotes that the entity has been flagged and is pending review by an admin.

values.name: STATE_SUSPENDED
values.description: Denotes that the entity has been reviewed and suspended by an admin.

messages.name: ErrorDetails
messages.description:
Error details that are communicated over gRPC (and HTTP) APIs.
The messages (for translation) are stored as "error:<namespace>:<name>".

fields.name: namespace
fields.description: Namespace of the error (typically the package name in the stack).

fields.name: name
fields.description: Name of the error.

fields.name: message_format
fields.description:
The default (fallback) message format that should be used for the error.
This is also used if the client does not have a translation for the error.

fields.name: attributes
fields.description:
Attributes that should be filled into the message format. Any extra attributes
can be displayed as error details.

fields.name: correlation_id
fields.description:
The correlation ID of the error can be used to correlate the error to stack
traces the network may (or may not) store about recent errors.

fields.name: cause
fields.description: The error that caused this error.

fields.name: collaborator
fields.description: Collaborator to grant all rights on the newly created gateway.

messages.name: Gateway
messages.description: Gateway is the message that defines a gateway on the network.

fields.name: cluster_address
fields.description: The address (host:port) of the Gateway Server to connect to.

fields.name: status_public
fields.description: The status of this gateway may be publicly displayed.

fields.name: location_public
fields.description: The location of this gateway may be publicly displayed.

fields.name: schedule_downlink_late
fields.description:
Enable server-side buffering of downlink messages. This is recommended for gateways using the Semtech UDP Packet
Forwarder v2.x or older, as it does not feature a just-in-time queue. If enabled, the Gateway Server schedules the
downlink message late to the gateway so that it does not overwrite previously scheduled downlink messages that have
not been transmitted yet.

fields.name: enforce_duty_cycle
fields.description:
Enforcing gateway duty cycle is recommended for all gateways to respect spectrum regulations. Disable enforcing the
duty cycle only in controlled research and development environments.

messages.name: GatewayAntenna
messages.description: GatewayAntenna is the message that defines a gateway antenna.

fields.name: gain
fields.description: gain is the antenna gain relative to this gateway, in dBi.

fields.name: location
fields.description: location is the antenna's location.

fields.name: logos
fields.description: Logos contains file names of brand logos.
fields.label: repeated

messages.name: GatewayConnectionStats
messages.description: Connection stats as monitored by the Gateway Server.

fields.name: protocol
fields.description: Protocol used to connect (for example, udp, mqtt, grpc)

fields.name: time
fields.description: Current time of the gateway

fields.name: boot_time
fields.description:
Boot time of the gateway
- can be left out to save bandwidth; old value will be kept

fields.name: versions
fields.description:
Versions of gateway subsystems
- each field can be left out to save bandwidth; old value will be kept
- map keys are written in snake_case
- for example:
    firmware: "2.0.4"
    forwarder: "v2-3.3.1"
    fpga: "48"
    dsp: "27"
    hal: "v2-3.5.0"
fields.label: repeated

fields.name: antenna_locations
fields.description:
Location of each gateway's antenna
- if left out, server uses registry-set location as fallback
fields.label: repeated

fields.name: ip
fields.description:
IP addresses of this gateway.
Repeated addresses can be used to communicate addresses of multiple interfaces (LAN, Public IP, ...).
fields.label: repeated

fields.name: metrics
fields.description:
Metrics
- can be used for forwarding gateway metrics such as temperatures or performance metrics
- map keys are written in snake_case
fields.label: repeated

fields.name: advanced
fields.description:
Advanced metadata fields
- can be used for advanced information or experimental features that are not yet formally defined in the API
- field names are written in snake_case

messages.name: RootKeys
messages.description:
Root keys for a LoRaWAN device.
These are stored on the Join Server.

fields.name: root_key_id
fields.description: Join Server issued identifier for the root keys.

fields.name: app_key
fields.description: The (encrypted) Application Key.

fields.name: nwk_key
fields.description: The (encrypted) Network Key.

messages.name: SessionKeys
messages.description:
Session keys for a LoRaWAN session.
Only the components for which the keys were meant, will have the key-encryption-key (KEK) to decrypt the individual keys.

fields.name: session_key_id
fields.description:
Join Server issued identifier for the session keys.
This ID can be used to request the keys from the Join Server in case the are lost.

fields.name: f_nwk_s_int_key
fields.description:
The (encrypted) Forwarding Network Session Integrity Key (or Network Session Key in 1.0 compatibility mode).
This key is stored by the (forwarding) Network Server.

fields.name: s_nwk_s_int_key
fields.description:
The (encrypted) Serving Network Session Integrity Key.
This key is stored by the (serving) Network Server.

fields.name: nwk_s_enc_key
fields.description:
The (encrypted) Network Session Encryption Key.
This key is stored by the (serving) Network Server.

fields.name: app_s_key
fields.description:
The (encrypted) Application Session Key.
This key is stored by the Application Server.

values.name: CONTEXT
values.description: Resets DevAddr, Session Keys, Frame Counters, Radio Parameters.

values.name: KEYS
values.description: Resets DevAddr, Session Keys, Frame Counters, while keeping the Radio Parameters.

fields.name: freq
fields.description:
Frequencies to be broadcasted, in hecto-Hz.
These values are broadcasted as 24 bits unsigned integers.
This field should not contain default values.
fields.label: repeated

fields.name: ch_masks
fields.description:
ChMasks controlling the channels to be used.
If this value is used, there should be 80 values.
fields.label: repeated

fields.name: opt_neg
fields.description: OptNeg is set if Network Server implements LoRaWAN 1.1 or greater.

fields.name: adr_ack_req
fields.description: Only on uplink.

fields.name: f_pending
fields.description: Only on downlink.

fields.name: class_b
fields.description: Only on uplink.

fields.name: adr_ack_limit_exponent
fields.description: Exponent e that configures the ADR_ACK_LIMIT = 2^e messages.

fields.name: adr_ack_delay_exponent
fields.description: Exponent e that configures the ADR_ACK_DELAY = 2^e messages.

fields.name: frequency
fields.description: Frequency of the Class B beacons (Hz).

fields.name: delay
fields.description: (uint16) See LoRaWAN specification.

fields.name: frequency
fields.description: Downlink channel frequency (Hz).

fields.name: battery
fields.description:
Device battery status.
0 indicates that the device is connected to an external power source.
1..254 indicates a battery level.
255 indicates that the device was not able to measure the battery level.

fields.name: margin
fields.description: SNR of the last downlink (dB; [-32, +31]).

fields.name: period_exponent
fields.description: Exponent e that configures the rejoin period = 32 * 2^e + rand(0,32) seconds.

fields.name: margin
fields.description: Indicates the link margin in dB of the received LinkCheckReq, relative to the demodulation floor.

fields.name: frequency
fields.description: Channel frequency (Hz).

fields.name: frequency
fields.description: Ping slot channel frequency (Hz).

fields.name: max_count_exponent
fields.description: Exponent e that configures the rejoin counter = 2^(e+4) messages.

fields.name: max_time_exponent
fields.description: Exponent e that configures the rejoin timer = 2^(e+10) seconds.

fields.name: rx2_frequency
fields.description: Rx2 frequency (Hz).

fields.name: max_eirp_index
fields.description:
Indicates the maximum EIRP value in dBm, indexed by the following vector:
[ 8 10 12 13 14 16 18 20 21 24 26 27 29 30 33 36 ]

fields.name: rejoin_cnt
fields.description: Contains RJCount0 or RJCount1 depending on rejoin_type.

messages.name: TxSettings
messages.description:
TxSettings contains the LoRaWAN settings for a transmission.
This message is used in both uplink and downlink

fields.name: data_rate_index
fields.description: LoRaWAN data rate index.

fields.name: bandwidth
fields.description: LoRa bandwidth (Hz).

fields.name: spreading_factor
fields.description: LoRa spreading factor.

fields.name: bit_rate
fields.description: FSK bit rate (bps).

fields.name: coding_rate
fields.description: LoRa coding rate.

fields.name: frequency
fields.description: Frequency (Hz).

fields.name: tx_power
fields.description: Transmission power (dBm). Only on downlink.

fields.name: invert_polarization
fields.description: Invert LoRa polarization; false for LoRaWAN uplink, true for downlink.

fields.name: channel_index
fields.description: Index of the channel that received the message.

fields.name: enable_crc
fields.description: Send a CRC in the packet; only on uplink; on downlink, CRC should not be enabled.

services.name: DownlinkMessageProcessor
services.description: The DownlinkMessageProcessor service processes downlink messages.

services.name: UplinkMessageProcessor
services.description: The UplinkMessageProcessor service processes uplink messages.

values.name: FORMATTER_NONE
values.description: No payload formatter to work with raw payload only.

values.name: FORMATTER_REPOSITORY
values.description: Use payload formatter for the end device type from a repository.

values.name: FORMATTER_GRPC_SERVICE
values.description: gRPC service payload formatter. The parameter is the host:port of the service.

values.name: FORMATTER_JAVASCRIPT
values.description: Custom payload formatter that executes Javascript code. The parameter is a JavaScript filename.

values.name: FORMATTER_CAYENNELPP
values.description:
CayenneLPP payload formatter.

More payload formatters can be added.

fields.name: session_key_id
fields.description: Join Server issued identifier for the session keys negotiated in this join.

fields.name: app_s_key
fields.description: Encrypted Application Session Key (if Join Server sent it to Network Server).

fields.name: session_key_id
fields.description: Join Server issued identifier for the session keys used by this uplink.

messages.name: DownlinkMessage
messages.description: Downlink message from the network to the end device

fields.name: up_formatter
fields.description: Payload formatter for uplink messages, must be set together with its parameter.

fields.name: up_formatter_parameter
fields.description: Parameter for the up_formatter, must be set together.

fields.name: down_formatter
fields.description: Payload formatter for downlink messages, must be set together with its parameter.

fields.name: down_formatter_parameter
fields.description: Parameter for the down_formatter, must be set together.

messages.name: UplinkMessage
messages.description: Uplink message from the end device to the network

fields.name: received_at
fields.description: Server time when the Gateway Server received the message.

values.name: SOURCE_UNKNOWN
values.description: The source of the location is not known or not set.

values.name: SOURCE_GPS
values.description: The location is determined by GPS.

values.name: SOURCE_REGISTRY
values.description: The location is set in and updated from a registry.

values.name: SOURCE_IP_GEOLOCATION
values.description: The location is estimated with IP geolocation.

values.name: SOURCE_WIFI_RSSI_GEOLOCATION
values.description: The location is estimated with WiFi RSSI geolocation.

values.name: SOURCE_BT_RSSI_GEOLOCATION
values.description: The location is estimated with BT/BLE RSSI geolocation.

values.name: SOURCE_LORA_RSSI_GEOLOCATION
values.description: The location is estimated with LoRa RSSI geolocation.

values.name: SOURCE_LORA_TDOA_GEOLOCATION
values.description: The location is estimated with LoRa TDOA geolocation.

values.name: SOURCE_COMBINED_GEOLOCATION
values.description:
The location is estimated by a combination of geolocation sources.

More estimation methods can be added.

fields.name: latitude
fields.description: The NorthSouth position (degrees; -90 to +90), where 0 is the equator, North pole is positive, South pole is negative.

fields.name: longitude
fields.description: The East-West position (degrees; -180 to +180), where 0 is the Prime Meridian (Greenwich), East is positive , West is negative.

fields.name: altitude
fields.description: The altitude (meters), where 0 is the mean sea level.

fields.name: accuracy
fields.description: The accuracy of the location (meters).

fields.name: source
fields.description: Source of the location information.

messages.name: RxMetadata
messages.description:
Contains metadata for a received message. Each antenna that receives
a message corresponds to one RxMetadata.

fields.name: timestamp
fields.description:
Gateway's internal timestamp when the Rx finished (nanoseconds)
NOTE: most gateways use microsecond timestamps, so conversion may be needed

fields.name: fine_timestamp
fields.description: Gateway's internal fine timestamp when the Rx finished (nanoseconds).

fields.name: encrypted_fine_timestamp
fields.description: Encrypted gateway's internal fine timestamp when the Rx finished (nanoseconds).

fields.name: rssi
fields.description: Received signal strength (dBm).

fields.name: channel_rssi
fields.description: Received channel power (dBm).

fields.name: rssi_standard_deviation
fields.description: Standard deviation of the RSSI.

fields.name: snr
fields.description: Signal-to-noise ratio (dB).

fields.name: frequency_offset
fields.description: Frequency offset (Hz).

fields.name: location
fields.description: Antenna location; injected by the Gateway Server.

fields.name: downlink_path_constraint
fields.description: Gateway downlink path constraint; injected by the Gateway Server.

fields.name: advanced
fields.description:
Advanced metadata fields
- can be used for advanced information or experimental features that are not yet formally defined in the API
- field names are written in snake_case

messages.name: TxMetadata
messages.description:
Contains metadata for a to-be-transmitted message.
It contains gateway-specific fields that are not in the TxSettings message

fields.name: advanced

Advanced metadata fields
- can be used for advanced information or experimental features that are not yet formally defined in the API
- field names are written in snake_case

services.name: AsNs
services.description: The AsNs service connects an Application Server to a Network Server.

services.name: GsNs
services.description: The GsNs service connects a Gateway Server to a Network Server.

services.name: NsDeviceRegistry
services.description: The NsDeviceRegistry service allows clients to manage their end devices on the Network Server.

methods.name: Get
methods.description:
Get returns the device that matches the given identifiers.
If there are multiple matches, an error will be returned.

methods.name: Set
methods.description: Set creates or updates the device.

methods.name: Delete
methods.description:
Delete deletes the device that matches the given identifiers.
If there are multiple matches, an error will be returned.

fields.name: collaborator
fields.description:
Collaborator to grant all rights on the newly created application.
NOTE: It is currently not possible to have organizations collaborating on
other organizations.

messages.name: ListOrganizationsRequest
messages.description:
By default we list all organizations the caller has rights on.
Set the user to instead list the organizations
where the user or organization is collaborator on.

fields.name: collaborator
fields.description:
NOTE: It is currently not possible to have organizations collaborating on
other organizations.

methods.name: UpdateAPIKey
methods.description:
Update the rights of an existing organization API key. To generate an API key,
the CreateAPIKey should be used. To delete an API key, update it
with zero rights.

methods.name: SetCollaborator
methods.description:
Set the rights of a collaborator (member) on the organization. Users
are considered to be a collaborator if they have at least one right on the
organization.
Note that only users can collaborate (be member of) an organization.

methods.name: Create
methods.description:
Create a new organization. This also sets the given user as
first collaborator with all possible rights.

methods.name: Get
methods.description:
Get the organization with the given identifiers, selecting the fields given
by the field mask. The method may return more or less fields, depending on
the rights of the caller.

methods.name: List
methods.description: List organizations. See request message for details.

fields.description: Received signal strength offset (dBm).

fields.description: Bandwidth (Hz).

enums.name: Right

values.name: RIGHT_USER_SETTINGS_BASIC
values.description: The right to edit basic user settings.

values.description: The right to delete user account.

values.name: RIGHT_USER_AUTHORIZED_CLIENTS
values.description: The right to view and edit authorized OAuth clients of the user.

values.name: RIGHT_USER_APPLICATIONS_LIST
values.description: The right to list applications the user is a collaborator of.

values.name: RIGHT_USER_ORGANIZATIONS_CREATE

values.name: RIGHT_USER_ALL

values.name: RIGHT_GATEWAY_TRAFFIC_DOWN_WRITE

The right to link as Gateway to a Gateway Server for traffic exchange,

values.name: RIGHT_ORGANIZATION_ALL

The right to send invite

note that this is not prefixed with "USER_"; it is not a right on the user entity.

values.name: RIGHT_ALL

services.name: EndDeviceRegistrySearch
services.description:
The EndDeviceRegistrySearch service indexes devices in the EndDeviceRegistry
and enables searching for them.
This service is not implemented on all deployments.

services.name: EntityRegistrySearch
services.description:
The EntityRegistrySearch service indexes entities in the various registries
and enables searching for them.
This service is not implemented on all deployments.

messages.name: User
messages.description: User is the message that defines an user on the network.

fields.name: primary_email_address
fields.description:
Primary email address that can be used for logging in.
This address is not public, use contact_info for that.

fields.name: password
fields.description: Only used on create; never returned.

fields.name: state
fields.description:
The reviewing state of the user.
This field can only be modified by admins.

fields.name: admin
fields.description:
This user is an admin.
This field can only be modified by other admins.

methods.name: UpdateAPIKey
methods.description:
Update the rights of an existing user API key. To generate an API key,
the CreateAPIKey should be used. To delete an API key, update it
with zero rights.

methods.name: Create
methods.description: Register a new user. This method may be restricted by network settings.

methods.name: Get
methods.description:
Get the user with the given identifiers, selecting the fields given by the
field mask. The method may return more or less fields, depending on the rights
of the caller.

scalarValueTypes.notes: Uses variable-length encoding. Inefficient for encoding negative numbers  if your field is likely to have negative values, use sint32 instead.
Uses variable-length encoding. Inefficient for encoding negative numbers  if your field is likely to have negative values, use sint64 instead.
Uses variable-length encoding. Signed int value. These more efficiently encode negative numbers than regular int32s.
Uses variable-length encoding. Signed int value. These more efficiently encode negative numbers than regular int64s.
Always four bytes. More efficient than uint32 if values are often greater than 2^28.
Always eight bytes. More efficient than uint64 if values are often greater than 2^56.
A string must always contain UTF-8 encoded or 7-bit ASCII text.
May contain any arbitrary sequence of bytes.
